HEADWORD: Underclay
<hw>Un"der*clay`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>A stratum of clay lying beneath a coal bed, often containing the
roots of coal plants, especially the <er>Stigmaria</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undercliff</ent>⟦br⟧
